title: Augustana Men's Basketball Ranked #1 In DII Bulletin Preseason Poll
text:
Augustana Men's Basketball Ranked #1 In DII Bulletin Preseason Poll POSTED: 11:47 AM CDT Oct 05, 2015 
The Division II Bulletin released its 2015-16 season preview on Monday morning. More from KDLT Scoreboard Friday, October 2nd 
The publication listed Augustana men's basketball as the No. 1 team in the country heading into the 2015-16 season. Augustana's Daniel Jansen and Casey Schilling were also named to the Division II Bulletin Preseason All-America Team. 
Augustana was picked at No. 2 in the Sporting News Yearbook preseason poll earlier this fall and Jansen and Schilling were also named preseason All-America by Sporting News. 
Augustana returns 12 players, including all five starters, from last season's team that finished 31-3 and set a program record for most wins. The Vikings also hosted the NCAA Central Region Tournament for the first time in program history. 
The Vikings won a share of the NSIC Regular Season Championship last season, finishing 20-2 in conference play and went on to win the first conference tournament in program history winning four straight games to capture the NSIC/Sanford Health Tournament title.
